abstract: In the last two weeks, four Republican state senators have said they will step down in 2020, giving Democrats hope of winning a supermajority.
snippet: In the last two weeks, four Republican state senators have said they will step down in 2020, giving Democrats hope of winning a supermajority.
lead_paragraph: ALBANY, N.Y. — Republicans in New York probably had hoped the worst was over.

abstract: The grounds of Milan’s Villa Belgiojoso are off limits to adults unaccompanied by a minor. But a city councilor wants to open the park to all ages.
snippet: The grounds of Milan’s Villa Belgiojoso are off limits to adults unaccompanied by a minor. But a city councilor wants to open the park to all ages.
lead_paragraph: On a recent Sunday, Silvia Rezzonico pushed a stroller through the glorious gardens of Villa Belgiojoso, winding past parents chasing their toddlers and families lounging on blankets.

headline_main: Emmanuel Carrère’s Disconcertingly Personal and Utterly Gripping Prose

abstract: If anyone understands the power of video, it is the N.F.L. But in a triumph of guerrilla filmmaking, Kaepernick keeps seizing their narrative control.
snippet: If anyone understands the power of video, it is the N.F.L. But in a triumph of guerrilla filmmaking, Kaepernick keeps seizing their narrative control.
lead_paragraph: On Nov. 16, Colin Kaepernick, the free-agent quarterback at the center of sports’ most contentious labor dispute, held a workout on the football field at Charles R. Drew High School in Riverdale, Ga., a dozen miles south of Atlanta. In a livestream broadcast by a local NBC affiliate, Kaepernick could be seen doing the stuff athletes usually do when they arrive at workouts: chatting with onlookers, milling around, tapping at a phone, limbering up. Eventually he was joined by four other players, all unsigned wide receivers, and he began to throw some footballs. This was the main event: a chance for viewers — and, more to the point, a group of N.F.L. team scouts — to assess the skills and fitness of Kaepernick, who is 32 and hasn’t played a snap in a game since the 2016 season.

abstract: Algerians — without a leader since April — voted on Thursday for a new president in an election marked by protests, scattered violence and a boycott by the massive pro-democracy movement that ousted President Abdelaziz Bouteflika.
snippet: Algerians — without a leader since April — voted on Thursday for a new president in an election marked by protests, scattered violence and a boycott by the massive pro-democracy movement that ousted President Abdelaziz Bouteflika.
lead_paragraph: ALGIERS, Algeria — Algerians — without a leader since April — voted on Thursday for a new president in an election marked by protests, scattered violence and a boycott by the massive pro-democracy movement that ousted President Abdelaziz Bouteflika.
headline_main: Algerians Choose Leader as Pro-Democracy Movement Boycotts
headline_print_headline: Algerians Choose Leader as Pro-Democracy Movement Boycotts

abstract: The International Ice Hockey Federation (IIHF) will try to ensure Russia retains the right to host the 2023 world ice hockey championship, IIHF President Rene Fasel said on Thursday.
snippet: The International Ice Hockey Federation (IIHF) will try to ensure Russia retains the right to host the 2023 world ice hockey championship, IIHF President Rene Fasel said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The International Ice Hockey Federation (IIHF) will try to ensure Russia retains the right to host the 2023 world ice hockey championship, IIHF President Rene Fasel said on Thursday.
headline_main: IIHF Says to Work to Keep 2023 World Championship in Russia
headline_print_headline: IIHF Says to Work to Keep 2023 World Championship in Russia

abstract: Global oil inventories could rise sharply despite OPEC and its allies deepening their output cuts and slowing U.S. production growth, the International Energy Agency (IEA) said on Thursday.
